{
  "texts": [
    "The GTNN transforms the graph into a condensed one-dimensional (1D) feature vector.",
    "Subsequently, this feature vector is decoded back into the corresponding molecular string, using a CLM based on an RNN-LSTM 32, 76 architecture for the molecule generation process.",
    "Graph transformer neural network.",
    "Message passing: The atomic features were embedded and transformed using a multilayer Perceptron (MLP) to obtain atomic feature vectors h 0 i.",
    "Message passing as suggested by Satorras et al."
  ]
}